criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Healthy adults from 18 to <55 years or 65 to <85 years at the time of enrollment
             (dependent upon study stage);

          -  If female of child-bearing potential and heterosexually active, must have practiced
             adequate contraception for 30 days prior to injection, have a negative pregnancy test
             on the day of injection, and have agreed to continue adequate contraception until 90
             days after the second injection. (Please refer to the glossary for the definition of
             child-bearing potential and adequate contraception);

          -  Able to provide consent to participate in and having signed an Informed Consent Form
             (ICF);

          -  Able and willing to complete all the scheduled study procedures during the whole study
             follow-up period (about 7 months);

          -  Negative result of HIV, hepatitis B and C screening;

          -  Oral temperature < 38.0ºC;

          -  Negative IgG and IgM antibodies against COVID-19, from RCT test;

          -  Negative result of real-time quantitative PCR screening of nasopharyngeal swabs/sputum
             for SARS-CoV-2;

          -  Hematological (including biochemistry) examination is within normal range, or no
             greater than a grade 1 abnormality and no clinical significance as assessed by the
             study investigator including: Complete Blood Count (CBC), hemoglobin (Hgb), platelets
             (PLT), prothrombin time (PT), partial thromboplastin time (PTT), alanine transaminase
             (ALT), aspartate transaminase (AST), alkaline phosphatase (ALP), total bilirubin (T
             Bil), creatinine (Cr), Lipase, and blood glucose,

          -  Transient mild laboratory abnormalities may be rescreened once, and the participant
             will be deemed eligible if the laboratory repeat test is normal as per local
             laboratory normal values.

          -  Good general health status, as determined by history and physical examination no
             greater than 14 days prior to administration of the test article.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Personal history of seizure disorder, encephalopathy or psychosis;

          -  Allergic history to any vaccine, or allergic to any vaccine ingredient;

          -  Woman who is pregnant (positive urine pregnancy test) or lactating, or plans to become
             pregnant during the next 3 months;

          -  Any acute febrile disease (oral temperature ≥38.0○C) or active infectious disease on
             the day of vaccination;

          -  Medical history of SARS (SARS-CoV-1);

          -  Serious cardiovascular diseases, such as arrhythmia, conduction block, history of
             myocardial infarction, severe hypertension not controlled with medication;

          -  Serious chronic disease such as asthma, diabetes and thyroid disease, etc.;

          -  Immunodeficiency, asplenia or functional asplenia;

          -  Platelet disorder or other bleeding disorder that may cause intramuscular injection
             contraindication;

          -  Immunosuppressive medication, anti-allergic, cytotoxic therapy, inhaled
             corticosteroids (excluding corticosteroid spray for allergic rhinitis, surface
             corticosteroid therapy for acute non-complicated dermatitis) in the last 6 months;

          -  Prior administration of blood products in last 4 months;

          -  Other vaccination(s) or investigational drugs within 1 month before study onset, or
             planned use during the study period;

          -  Prior administration of any live attenuated vaccine within 1 month before study onset;

          -  Prior administration of subunit or inactivated non-SARS-CoV-2 vaccine within 1 month
             before study onset;

          -  Prior administration of any other vaccine considered (or being considered) to protect
             against SARS-CoV-2 any time before study onset or during study period;

          -  Prior participation in other studies involving study intervention containing lipid
             nanoparticles;

          -  Any condition that, in the opinion of the investigators, may interfere with the
             participant's compliance or evaluation of study objectives or informed consent (i.e.
             medical, psychological, social or other conditions, etc.);

          -  Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), current smoker or vaper.

          -  History of hypertension.

          -  History or diagnosis of coagulopathies.

          -  Body mass index (BMI) >30kg/m2.

          -  High risk of acquiring SARS-CoV-2 infection due to surroundings, contacts or
             circumstances. Explicitly exclude healthcare and "essential workers"/at risk
             population.
